                <head>81. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>Concerns in the Government of Japan about the <persName corresp="#p_KJF2"
                        >Kennedy</persName> administration’s proposed interest equalization tax
                    prompted Japanese Foreign Minister Masayoshi Ohira to come to Washington for
                    discussions with senior U.S. officials. He met separately with Under Secretary
                        <persName corresp="#p_BGW1">Ball</persName> and Secretary <persName
                        corresp="#p_RD3">Rusk</persName> on August 1 and with President <persName
                        corresp="#p_KJF2">Kennedy</persName> on August 2, 1963. Memoranda of all
                    three conversations are scheduled for publication in <ref
                        target="frus1961-63v22">volume XXII</ref>. Regarding earlier Japanese
                    complaints on this question, see <ref target="#d79">Document 79</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
